There was a large turnout of supporters in Ekiti on Thursday as the Labour Party (LP) held its presidential campaign rally in the state. Peter Obi, LP presidential candidate; Julius Abure, national chairperson of the party; and Akin Osuntokun, the director-general of the LP presidential campaign council, were among those in attendance. Odunayo Okunade, LP chairperson in Ekiti, was among party stakeholders in the state who were also at the event. See pictures below.           